---
By: Henry D. Thoreau
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 433
    Verse: 3
Tags:
  - Simplicity
---
Simplicity, simplicity, simplicity! I say let your affairs be as one, two,
three and not a hundred or a thousand. ...We are happy in proportion to the
things we can do without.
